<br>
The Government does NOT 'exist' to correct Market Failures.  However, as a consequence of its existing, it does correct Market Failures.<br>
<br>
The United States (hereafter referred to as the Government) exists to perform all necessary functions to run this country - it collects taxes so it has funds to do so, it maintains armies, law enfoircement, legislative and judicial functions, it runs national trusts, regulates business and commercial interests, settles disputes between states, etc.<br>
<br>
The simplistic statement of the Government 'existing to correct market failures' is true in the same way as saying &quot;I exist in order to consume food and poop.&quot;  It is not an accurate definition, although it is true that I eat and poop.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> If the governement wasn't responsible for correcting market failures, (via the definition) <br>
